FBIS4-15234 "drsov067_b_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Appoints Shakhray Deputy Prime Minister Yeltsin Appoints Shakhray Deputy Prime Minister LD0704120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1135 GMT 7 Apr 94 LD0704120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow April 7 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin has appointed Nationalities Minister Sergey Shakhray as deputy prime minister, the press service of the president reported today. Thus the number of deputy prime ministers amounted to six, including one first deputy.
